{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775815886678,"sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","part":{"id":"prt_d76e00753001tKB0YvhY2PLqSc","messageID":"msg_d76e0027c001DNtVGJw54oxe2y","sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775815887563,"sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","part":{"id":"prt_d76e008d00016sXJtK8WQteTtH","messageID":"msg_d76e0027c001DNtVGJw54oxe2y","sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b47b2acf551c44e5a6100c5f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Orchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\n9: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n13: - **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n14: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\n17: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n20: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`\n21: - **WHEN** the template is deserialized\n22: - **THEN** `labels` and `annotations` are optional maps and `spec` is required and of type `corev1.PodSpec`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status\n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with optional `conditions` of type `[]metav1.Condition`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Conditions optional\n28: - **GIVEN** a minimal `AgentRuntime` object\n29: - **WHEN** status is omitted or empty\n30: - **THEN** deserialization succeeds without requiring `conditions`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n33: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the same API group/version with subresource `status` and print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter GVR\n36: - **GIVEN** dynamic client configuration for workload templates\n37: - **WHEN** GVR is constructed for `codeinterpreters`\n38: - **THEN** group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, resource `codeinterpreters`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with: optional `Ports` (`[]TargetPort`, JSON `ports`); required `Template` (`*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, JSON `template`); optional `SessionTimeout` with default `\"15m\"`; optional `MaxSessionDuration` with default `\"8h\"`; optional `WarmPoolSize` (`*int32`); optional `AuthMode` (`AuthModeType`, JSON `authMode`) with default `\"picod\"` and enum `picod` or `none`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Auth mode constants\n44: - **GIVEN** API constants for auth mode\n45: - **WHEN** `AuthMode` is compared\n46: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` equals `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` equals `\"none\"`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n49: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with optional `conditions` and optional boolean `ready`.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Ready flag\n52: - **GIVEN** a reconciled `CodeInterpreter`\n53: - **WHEN** status is updated by the controller\n54: - **THEN** `status.ready` may be set to `true` alongside a `Ready` condition\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: TargetPort and Protocol types\n57: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` with optional `pathPrefix`, optional `name`, required `port` (`uint32`), and required `protocol` (`ProtocolType`) with kubebuilder default `HTTP` and enum `HTTP` or `HTTPS`.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Protocol constants\n60: - **GIVEN** port configuration without explicit protocol in some code paths\n61: - **WHEN** defaults apply at API level\n62: - **THEN** default protocol is `HTTP` per kubebuilder marker\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Workload manager health endpoint\n65: The system SHALL serve `GET /health` without authentication and SHALL respond `200` with JSON body `{\"status\":\"healthy\"}`.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Health bypasses auth middleware\n68: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n69: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` with no `Authorization` header\n70: - **THEN** the response status is 200 and body contains `\"status\":\"healthy\"`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Workload manager v1 routes and middleware\n73: The system SHALL mount a `/v1` route group with `loggingMiddleware` then `authMiddleware` (order preserved), and SHALL register `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session id path parameter\n76: - **GIVEN** a delete request\n77: - **WHEN** Gin binds the path\n78: - **THEN** the session identifier is read from parameter name `sessionId` (camelCase)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Create sandbox request validation\n81: The system SHALL accept JSON for create endpoints matching `CreateSandboxRequest` with fields `kind`, `name`, `namespace`; SHALL overwrite `kind` from the handler (`AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`); and SHALL reject requests where `kind` is not one of those, `namespace` is empty, or `name` is empty.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Validation failure returns 400\n84: - **GIVEN** the handler sets `sandboxReq.Kind` from the route and `Validate()` is called\n85: - **WHEN** `namespace` or `name` is empty in the JSON body\n86: - **THEN** the response is 400 and the error message includes `required` (e.g. `namespace is required` or `name is required`)\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create sandbox success response\n89: On successful creation the system SHALL respond `200` with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing `sessionId`, `sandboxId`, `sandboxName`, and `entryPoints` (each entry point has `path`, `protocol`, `endpoint`).\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Entry points reflect TargetPort and pod IP\n92: - **GIVEN** a sandbox reaches running state and pod IP is resolved\n93: - **WHEN** the response is built\n94: - **THEN** each entry point `endpoint` is `host:port` joined from pod IP and configured port, with protocol string from `TargetPort.Protocol`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Create sandbox error responses\n97: The system SHALL return `400` with `{\"message\":...}` for invalid JSON or validation failure; `404` with message from wrapped not-found errors when AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is missing from informer cache; `401` with message from client extraction error when `EnableAuth` is true; `500` with `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}` for other create failures including timeout.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: JSON parse failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a non-JSON body to `POST /v1/agent-runtime`\n101: - **WHEN** the handler binds JSON\n102: - **THEN** status is 400 and message is `Invalid request body`\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Optional Bearer authentication via TokenReview\n105: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` with exactly two space-separated fields; SHALL validate via `authentication/v1` `TokenReview` create; SHALL cache results in an LRU cache (capacity 1000, entry TTL 5 minutes); and SHALL store in context: token, full username, service account name, namespace parsed from `system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<name>`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Missing header\n108: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n109: - **WHEN** `/v1/...` is called without `Authorization`\n110: - **THEN** response is 401 with message `Missing authorization header` and handler chain aborts\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: TokenReview success path\n113: - **GIVEN** a valid service account token and `EnableAuth` true\n114: - **WHEN** `validateServiceAccountToken` runs with cache miss\n115: - **THEN** the server creates `TokenReview` with `spec.token` set and uses `status.user.username` when `status.authenticated` is true\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Authenticated Kubernetes operations use user client\n118: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL use a per-user dynamic client (from bearer token) for creating/deleting `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` resources; when false, SHALL use the manager’s in-cluster/default dynamic client.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: User client cache key\n121: - **GIVEN** repeated requests from the same namespace and service account name\n122: - **WHEN** `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient` is used\n123: - **THEN** the cache key is `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation ordering and store placeholder\n126: The system SHALL call `StoreSandbox` with a placeholder `SandboxInfo` before creating the `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` in the API; SHALL register a one-shot watcher before create; SHALL wait up to 2 minutes for sandbox status `running` from the reconciler; SHALL resolve pod IP and then `UpdateSandbox` with full info; and SHALL roll back the created CR on failure after the wait (delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim within a 30s timeout context).\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Watcher registration before create\n129: - **GIVEN** a create request reaches `createSandbox`\n130: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is created\n131: - **THEN** `WatchSandboxOnce` was already invoked for that namespace/name\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Timeout returns error\n134: - **GIVEN** no running notification within 2 minutes\n135: - **WHEN** the select completes\n136: - **THEN** creation fails with error `sandbox creation timed out` and HTTP 500 is returned to the client\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Pod IP resolution\n139: The system SHALL prefer pod name equal to sandbox name; if annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` exists on the created Sandbox (from agent-sandbox controller), SHALL use that as pod name; SHALL load pod from informer cache and require `PodRunning` and non-empty `PodIP`; otherwise SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>` and pick the pod whose controller owner reference is kind `Sandbox` and name matches.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Pod not running yields error\n142: - **GIVEN** a matching pod in non-Running phase\n143: - **WHEN** IP is resolved\n144: - **THEN** resolution fails with an error indicating the pod is not running\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Delete sandbox by session\n147: The system SHALL load session from store by `sessionId`; on `ErrNotFound` return `404` with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`; delete `SandboxClaim` when stored `Kind` is `SandboxClaim`, else delete `Sandbox`; treat API `NotFound` on delete as success; then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`; success response `200` `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store miss\n150: - **GIVEN** no session key in store\n151: - **WHEN** DELETE is invoked\n152: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404 and message mentions the session id\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: Garbage collection loop\n155: The system SHALL run a background goroutine tick every 15 seconds; each tick SHALL use a context timeout of 2 minutes; SHALL query inactive sessions with cutoff `now - 15m` and batch limit 16; SHALL query expired sessions with `before = now` and batch limit 16; SHALL merge lists and delete each unique workload then remove store entry by session ID.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: GC uses DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout\n158: - **GIVEN** GC lists inactive sandboxes\n159: - **WHEN** computing the inactive cutoff\n160: - **THEN** `inactiveTime` equals `time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)` where `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` is 15 minutes\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: HTTP server and process behavior\n163: The system SHALL use Gin with `gin.New()` for the workload API; SHALL serve with `h2c` wrapping and `http2.Server`; SHALL use `ReadTimeout` 15s and `IdleTimeout` 90s for HTTP when not using TLS; SHALL ping the store before listening; SHALL sync informers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod) with up to 1 minute wait; on SIGINT/SIGTERM SHALL shutdown HTTP within 15s, cancel context, wait for background workers, then `Close()` the store.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: TLS requires cert and key\n166: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` is true and cert or key path is empty\n167: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n168: - **THEN** it returns an error that TLS is enabled but cert/key not provided\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: API error helper constants\n171: The system SHALL define in package `api` the sentinel errors `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound`, `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound`, `ErrTemplateMissing`, `ErrPublicKeyMissing`, and SHALL map `CodeInterpreter` kind to group-resource `agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` and default kinds to `agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` for `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError`.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session not found uses API machinery\n174: - **GIVEN** `NewSessionNotFoundError(\"sid\")`\n175: - **WHEN** the error is inspected as `APIStatus`\n176: - **THEN** the group resource is `agentcube.volcano.sh, Resource=sessions` and name is the session id\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n\n## Purpose\nOrchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\nThe system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n\n#### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n- **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md","time":{"start":1775815887556,"end":1775815887561}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775815888215,"sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","part":{"id":"prt_d76e00b9c0010iuLVAHhi3oNt3","messageID":"msg_d76e0027c001DNtVGJw54oxe2y","sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3ed7735f2026423d91c33c72","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-store/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-store/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n9: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n12: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n13: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n14: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n17: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n20: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n21: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n22: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n25: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Key construction\n28: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n29: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n30: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n33: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n36: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n37: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n38: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n41: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n44: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n45: - **WHEN** executed\n46: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n49: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n52: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n53: - **WHEN** called\n54: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n57: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n60: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n61: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n62: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n65: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Full removal\n68: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n69: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n70: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n73: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n76: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n77: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n78: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n81: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n84: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n85: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n86: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n89: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Default redis\n92: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n93: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n94: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n97: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n100: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n101: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n102: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n105: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n108: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n109: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n110: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n113: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n116: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n117: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n118: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store Specification\n\n## Purpose\nPersist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n\n### Requirement: Not found semantics\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/session-store/spec.md","time":{"start":1775815888209,"end":1775815888214}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775815888861,"sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","part":{"id":"prt_d76e00ddd0012JEdEbbTu5chvO","messageID":"msg_d76e0027c001DNtVGJw54oxe2y","sessionID":"ses_289236096ffeVNwHYTDZO0EFx7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e254e095b90641098f587f4d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Code Execution (PicoD) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Command execution API\n10: \n11: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/execute` with a JSON body, run `command[0]` with `command[1:]` as arguments via `exec.CommandContext`, capture stdout and stderr into buffers, and respond with HTTP 200 and an `ExecuteResponse` for successful request handling (including non-zero command exit). The request SHALL NOT accept stdin from the client; the process stdin is not set from the request body.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Valid execution with defaults\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body with non-empty `command` and empty `timeout`\n16: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n17: - **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` (seconds), `start_time`, and `end_time` as JSON\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Custom timeout\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body where `timeout` is a non-empty string parseable by Go `time.ParseDuration` (e.g. `\"30s\"`, `\"500ms\"`)\n22: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n23: - **THEN** the server uses that duration for the command context timeout\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Timeout exceeded\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** execution exceeds the context deadline\n28: - **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n29: - **THEN** the response `exit_code` SHALL be `124` (`TimeoutExitCode`) and stderr SHALL include a message that the command timed out with the timeout length in seconds (integer formatting)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Invalid timeout\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `timeout` is non-empty and not a valid duration\n34: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n35: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON `error` describing invalid timeout format and `code` 400\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Empty command\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** JSON binds successfully but `command` has length zero\n40: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n41: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"command cannot be empty\"` and `code` 400\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Working directory inside workspace\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `working_dir` is non-empty\n46: - **WHEN** the server resolves it with the same path-safety rules as file APIs\n47: - **THEN** `cmd.Dir` is set to the sanitized absolute path; if resolution fails, the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` prefixed by `\"Invalid working directory: \"`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Environment augmentation\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** `env` is non-empty\n52: - **WHEN** the command runs\n53: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` is the current process environment plus additional entries `key=value` for each map entry\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Malformed JSON\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** the body is not valid JSON for `ExecuteRequest`\n58: - **WHEN** binding fails\n59: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` from the binder and `code` 400\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: File upload API\n62: \n63: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files`. If `Content-Type` starts with `multipart/form-data`, the server SHALL treat the request as multipart upload; otherwise it SHALL bind JSON for `UploadFileRequest`.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Multipart upload\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** `Content-Type` has prefix `multipart/form-data`, form field `path` is set, and form file `file` is present\n68: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n69: - **THEN** the server creates parent directories with mode `0755`, writes the uploaded stream to a sanitized path, applies mode from form field `mode` via `parseFileMode` (default `0644` when empty/invalid/exceeds max), and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` using `path` as relative to the workspace root\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Multipart missing path or file\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** multipart request with empty `path` or missing/unreadable `file`\n74: - **WHEN** the handler runs\n75: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with an appropriate `error` and `code` 400\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: JSON Base64 upload\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** non-multipart request with JSON `path` and `content` (Base64 standard encoding) required\n80: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n81: - **THEN** the server decodes content, creates directories, writes the file with `parseFileMode` on `mode`, and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` (relative `path`)\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Invalid Base64\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** JSON upload with invalid Base64 in `content`\n86: - **WHEN** decoding fails\n87: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing invalid base64 and `code` 400\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: File listing API\n90: \n91: The system SHALL accept `GET /api/files?path=...`, require the `path` query parameter, read the directory at the sanitized path, and return JSON `ListFilesResponse`.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Successful listing\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `path` refers to an existing directory inside the workspace\n96: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files?path=<dir>`\n97: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `files` as an array of `FileEntry` objects (`name`, `size`, `modified`, `mode`, `is_dir`), skipping entries where `entry.Info()` fails\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Missing query parameter\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** the `path` query parameter is absent or empty\n102: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files`\n103: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"Missing 'path' query parameter\"` and `code` 400\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Directory not found\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** sanitized path does not exist\n108: - **WHEN** `os.ReadDir` fails with not exist\n109: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` `\"Directory not found\"` and `code` 404\n110: \n111: ### Requirement: File download API\n112: \n113: The system SHALL serve file contents at `GET /api/files/*path` for a sanitized file path, set download-oriented headers, and stream the file with `c.File`.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Successful download\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** the wildcard path resolves to a regular file inside the workspace\n118: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/<path>`\n119: - **THEN** the server sets `Content-Description` to `File Transfer`, `Content-Transfer-Encoding` to `binary`, `Content-Disposition` to `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`, `Content-Type` from `mime.TypeByExtension` or `application/octet-stream`, and returns the file body\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Path escapes workspace\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the requested path fails `sanitizePath`\n124: - **WHEN** the client calls the download endpoint\n125: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing access denied / workspace jail\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Not a file\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** the path exists but is a directory\n130: - **WHEN** the client downloads\n131: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"Path is a directory, not a file\"` and `code` 400\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: File missing\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** the path does not exist\n136: - **WHEN** stat fails with not exist\n137: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` `\"File not found\"` and `code` 404\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Health endpoint\n140: \n141: The system SHALL expose `GET /health` without JWT middleware and respond HTTP 200 with JSON including `status`, `service`, `version`, and `uptime`.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Unauthenticated health\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** no `Authorization` header\n146: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /health`\n147: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `status` `\"ok\"`, `service` `\"PicoD\"`, `version` `\"0.0.1\"`, and `uptime` as a string from `time.Since(server start)`\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: JWT authentication for API routes\n150: \n151: The system SHALL register `/api` routes under a Gin group that uses `AuthManager.AuthMiddleware`. The middleware SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`, parse the JWT with an RSA public key, and reject non-RSA signing methods. Valid tokens SHALL allow the request to proceed; after validation the request body SHALL be wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` limiting size to `MaxBodySize`.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Missing or malformed Authorization\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** missing header, or a header that is not exactly two space-separated parts with first part `Bearer`\n156: - **WHEN** an `/api` route is hit\n157: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with JSON including `error`, `code` 401, and `detail` explaining the failure\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Invalid or expired JWT\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** a Bearer token that fails verification (signature, expiry, etc.) with options `WithExpirationRequired`, `WithIssuedAt`, and `WithLeeway(1 minute)`\n162: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n163: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with `error` `\"Invalid token\"`, `code` 401, and `detail` containing the verification error\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Public key required at startup\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is unset or does not decode to an RSA public key in PEM form\n168: - **WHEN** `NewServer` initializes\n169: - **THEN** the process SHALL log a fatal error and not continue serving (there is no unauthenticated API mode when the key is missing)\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Server configuration\n172: \n173: The system SHALL read CLI flags `-port` and `-workspace`, build `picod.Config`, and listen on `\":<port>\"`. If `workspace` is empty, the workspace root SHALL be the current working directory (fatal if `os.Getwd` fails). The HTTP server SHALL use `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Defaults from CLI\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** `-port` and `-workspace` use program defaults\n178: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n179: - **THEN** `port` defaults to `8080`, `workspace` defaults to empty (resolved to CWD), and Gin runs in `ReleaseMode` with `Logger` and `Recovery` middleware globally\n\n(End of file - total 179 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Code Execution (PicoD) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Command execution API\n\nThe system SHALL accept `POST /api/execute` with a JSON body, run `command[0]` with `command[1:]` as arguments via `exec.CommandContext`, capture stdout and stderr into buffers, and respond with HTTP 200 and an `ExecuteResponse` for successful request handling (including non-zero command exit). The request SHALL NOT accept stdin from the client; the process stdin is not set from the request body.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid execution with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body with non-empty `command` and empty `timeout`\n- **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n- **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` (seconds), `start_time`, and `end_time` as JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/code-execution/spec.md","time":{"start":1775815888854,"end":1775815888859}}}}
